Unless I have come to the wrong conclusion, only an individual who has been granted Administer Projects permission may control the suppression of the e-mail on a bulk issue change.

It is important for us to allow a broader set of project users to both make bulk changes and suppress the resulting e-mails.  It appears that the only way to support this is by adding additional project administrators.  Unfortunately that also grants other powers, like updating project user/role assignments.  This then grants more people to temporarily give and remove project roles for themselves and others that they know may give other powers, i.e. delete all comments, edit all comments, which do not have a History audit trail.

The ability to suppress a bulk change e-mail should be it's own standalone permission on the permission screen.  (really, bulk changes should be a project permission and not a global permission, so if you want to solve both of those, that'd be great).

